ProtoResult:
. "[Legendre Symbol of $2$] Let $p$ be an odd prime. Then $$ 
   (\frac{2}{p} ) = \begin{cases} \hfill1 & if p\equiv \pm 
   1\pmod{8}\\ -1 & if p\equiv \pm 3\pmod{8}. \end{cases} $$"
